ation of women, writing, and right conduct. This edition also includes a translation of an oration, or harangue, of Scudéry's in which Sapho extols the talents and abilities of women in order to persuade them to write.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aFrench literaturey17th centuryvTranslations into English. 0aWomenzFrancexSocial conditionsy17th centuryvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aromance, feminism, france, women writers, female authors, artamene ou le grand cyrus, marriage, gender, salon, novel, literature, love, sexuality, freedom, liberty, slavery, womens roles, education, writing, conduct, choice, artist, harangue, feminist theory, translation, archive, recovered text, canon, les femmes illustres, talent, ability, virtue.1 aNewman, Karen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226144009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226144009/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles